Mr. Donald Yontosh, in the form of a motion, recommended to approve Kevin Hubler as
Middle School Principal, at a starting salary of $75,000 effective January 1, 2023. Mrs.
Christina Brown seconded the motion, and it carried with a vote of 7-2-0. Voice Roll Call:
Mrs. Brown —- yes; Mr. Smeal — no; Mr. Diviney — yes; Mr. Yontosh — yes: Mr. Emigh

- yes; Mr. Dobo — yes; Mr. Seprish — yes; Ms. Maines - no; Mr. Parks — yes. Mr. Hubler
was in attendance. Mr. Diviney expressed that he was happy to have him aboard. Mr.
Hubler said it has been a great 14 years, and that he is excited for the next step.

Mr. Donald Yontosh, in the form of a motion, recommended to approve Sarah Koot as
School Psychologist, at a starting salary of $62,511 (Step 11M+45). (Start date pending
release from current school.) Ms. Jessica Maines seconded the motion, and it carried with
a vote of 9-0-0. Mr. Diviney asked if there would be a 60-day hold at Ms. Koot’s current
District. Mrs. Dutrow confirmed that there would be a 60-day hold per a conversation
with the previous District’s Administration.

Mr. Melvin Smeal, in the form of a motion, recommended to Motion to approve summer
hours (2023) for Sarah Koot, School Psychologist, for up to 20 days (not to exceed
$6,768). Ms. Jessica Maines seconded the motion, and it carried with a vote of 9-0-0.

